            <!-- The translation is given after S. Pou with slight modifications because of new reading in lines 4, 6, 7, 9 and 11. -->
<!-- argr: follow what the EG says about credit notes. -->
           <p n="1-5">Rizière en offrande de Poñ Vinayaśiva, mesurant 3 <foreign>mās</foreign>, d'un prix équivalant à 1 <foreign>liṅ</foreign> d'argent blanc, 6 <foreign>yau</foreign> de vêtements doubles, 1 <foreign>yau</foreign> de couverture : cela devint propriété du dieu Utpanna.</p>
            <p n="5-8">Voici d'autres champs et rizières, offerts par Poñ Kheṅ/Khoṅ, soit 1 <foreign>mās</foreign>, par Poñ Vidyādeva, soit 1 <foreign>mās</foreign>. Un serviteur <supplied reason="subaudible">nommé</supplied> ... offert au dieu, et 3 paires de boeufs.</p>
            <p n="9-10">Sacrifice au dieu chaque jour, 2 <foreign>liḥ</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation">de riz?</supplied>, et 3 <foreign>yau</foreign> d'étoffe pour chaque année.</p>
            <p n="10-13"><supplied reason="explanation">Texte décousu à cause des dégâts.</supplied></p>
         </div>
           <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng" resp="part:kuch">
             <p n="1-5">Paddy field offered by Poñ Vinayaśiva, measuring 3 <foreign>mās</foreign>, with a price equal to 1 <foreign>liṅ</foreign> of white silver, 6 <foreign>yau</foreign> of pairs of cloth, 1 <foreign>yau</foreign> of blanket : all this was the propriety of god Utpanna.</p>
              <p n="5-8">Here are other plantations and paddy fields, offered by Poñ Kheṅ/Khoṅ, equal to 1 <foreign>mās</foreign>, by Poñ Vidyādeva, equal to 1 <foreign>mās</foreign>. A servant <supplied reason="subaudible">by name</supplied> ... offered to the god and 3 pairs of cows.</p>
              <p n="9-10">Sacrifice to the god everyday, 2 <foreign>liḥ</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation">of rice?</supplied>, and 3 <foreign>yau</foreign> of cloth every year.</p>
              <p n="10-13"><supplied reason="explanation">Text is too damaged.</supplied></p>
